article.headline: Weber State 68, Portland State 63
article.story: PORTLAND, Ore. (AP) -- Lance Allred had 21 points to lead four players in double figures as Weber State rallied for a 68-63 win at Portland State. Nic Sparrow scored 18 points for the Wildcats (3-3, 10-9). John Hamilton added 14 points and Slobodan Ocokoljic had 10. Antone Jarrell led Portland State (2-4, 8-11) with 20 points. Marshall Hartman added a season-high 13 points for the Vikings. Trailing 40-33 at the half, Weber State stayed close during most of the second half. A runner by Hamilton capped a 9-2 run that gave the Wildcats a 61-59 lead with 3:38 left. It was their first lead since 2-0 and they would not trail again. The Portland State offense, which shot 64 percent in the first half, went cold late in the game and scored only six points in the last 8:20. Weber State, despite being outscored 42-20 in the paint, outrebounded the Vikings 34-17 and shot 49 percent for the game. ^
